  "plan": "# Restaurant Booking Eval Implementation Plan\n\n## Scope\n- Build one .NET 10 minimal Web API and one React + TypeScript SPA using in-memory persistence.\n- Keep architecture lightweight: vertical feature slices, pure booking-domain functions, thin endpoint/store shells, and explicit Result-style business errors.\n- Seed a small deterministic dataset of restaurants and tables so tests and UI behavior are predictable.\n\n## TDD Approach\n- Work one vertical behavior at a time: write one failing behavior test, implement the smallest passing API/domain code, then refactor.\n- Put conflict, validation, and availability rules in pure functions so boundary tests do not need mocks.\n- Test endpoints through the public API where practical, with focused pure-domain tests for dense booking rules.\n\n## Backend Slices\n1. Project and API shell\n- Create a .NET 10 solution with `src/RestaurantBooking.Api` and `tests/RestaurantBooking.Api.Tests`.\n- Enable nullable reference types, OpenAPI/Swagger, ProblemDetails, CORS for the SPA, and warning-free builds.\n- Add an in-memory singleton store seeded with restaurants, tables, and empty bookings.\n\n2. Restaurant list\n- Add `GET /api/restaurants` returning seeded restaurants and table capacity summaries.\n- Cover the route with a public API test.\n\n3. Booking domain core\n- Model restaurants, tables, bookings, requested time ranges, and booking confirmations.\n- Add pure functions for request validation, overlap detection, table selection, booking creation decisions, and slot availability.\n- Return Result-style errors for expected failures: `UnknownRestaurant`, `InvalidPartySize`, `InvalidDateTime`, `NoAvailability`, and `OverlappingReservation`.\n\n4. Create booking\n- Add `POST /api/bookings` to validate input, prevent overlapping reservations, persist successful bookings atomically in memory, and return confirmation.\n- Add boundary tests for invalid party size, invalid date/time, unknown restaurant, overlapping reservation, exact edge non-overlap, and successful booking.\n\n5. Availability and existing bookings\n- Add `GET /api/restaurants/{restaurantId}/availability?date=YYYY-MM-DD&partySize=N` returning deterministic slots within opening hours.\n- Add `GET /api/bookings` returning existing bookings for the UI.\n- Add tests for capacity filtering, reserved-slot exclusion, invalid date, invalid party size, and unknown restaurant.\n\n## Frontend Slices\n1. SPA setup\n- Create a React + TypeScript + Vite app under `frontend` with deterministic scripts: `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, and `deadcode`.\n- Keep dependencies minimal and configure ESLint, Prettier, and a dead-code checker such as Knip.\n\n2. API client services\n- Add typed service functions for listing restaurants, listing bookings, fetching availability, and creating bookings.\n- Centralize API base URL handling and map API errors into clear client-side messages.\n\n3. Booking UI\n- Show restaurant list, selected restaurant details, date/party-size inputs, available slots, booking form fields, booking confirmation, and existing bookings.\n- Keep state local and simple; refresh availability and bookings after successful booking.\n\n## README And Verification\n- Add README instructions for prerequisites, backend run/test/format commands, frontend install/run/check commands, and Swagger/API URLs.\n- Final backend checks: `dotnet build -p:TreatWarningsAsErrors=true`, `dotnet test --no-build`, and `dotnet format --verify-no-changes`.\n- Final frontend checks: dependency install plus `npm run build`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run lint`, `npm run format:check`, and `npm run deadcode`.\n",
